		</li>
		<li class="ibox-similarto clearfix">
			<div class="ibox-label">Similar to</div>
			<div class="ibox-info"><ul class="smw-format ul-format"><li class="smw-row"><span class="smw-field"><span class="smw-value"><a href="Simple_&quot;noun_+_adjective&quot;_sentences" title="Simple &quot;noun + adjective&quot; sentences">Simple "noun + adjective" sentences</a></span></span> (<span class="smw-field"><span class="smw-value">A1</span></span>)</li><li class="smw-row"><span class="smw-field"><span class="smw-value"><a href="Expressing_&quot;both…_and…&quot;_with_&quot;ji...you&quot;" title="Expressing &quot;both… and…&quot; with &quot;ji...you&quot;">Expressing "both… and…" with "ji...you"</a></span></span> (<span class="smw-field"><span class="smw-value">B2</span></span>)</li></ul></div>
		</li>
		<li class="ibox-similarto-hsk clearfix" style="display:none;">
			<div class="ibox-label">Similar to</div>
			<div class="ibox-info"><ul class="smw-format ul-format"><li class="smw-row"><span class="smw-field"><span class="smw-value"><a href="Simple_&quot;noun_+_adjective&quot;_sentences" title="Simple &quot;noun + adjective&quot; sentences">Simple "noun + adjective" sentences</a></span></span> (<span class="smw-field"><span class="smw-value">HSK1</span></span>)</li><li class="smw-row"><span class="smw-field"><span class="smw-value"><a href="Expressing_&quot;both…_and…&quot;_with_&quot;ji...you&quot;" title="Expressing &quot;both… and…&quot; with &quot;ji...you&quot;">Expressing "both… and…" with "ji...you"</a></span></span> (<span class="smw-field"><span class="smw-value">HSK4</span></span>)</li></ul></div>
		</li>
		<li class="ibox-usedfor clearfix">
			<div class="ibox-label">Used for</div>
			<div class="ibox-info"><a href="Describing_things" title="Describing things">Describing things</a>, <a href="Expressing_quality" title="Expressing quality">Expressing quality</a> </div>
		</li>
		<li class="ibox-keywords clearfix">
			<div class="ibox-label">Keywords</div>
			<div class="ibox-info"><a href="又" title="又">又</a></div>
		</li>
		
	</ul>
	<div class="ibox-image"><a href="./File:Chinese-grammar-wiki-you-2.jpg" class="image"><img alt="Chinese-grammar-wiki-you-2.jpg" src="https://resources.allsetlearning.com/gramwiki/images/thumb/2/24/Chinese-grammar-wiki-you-2.jpg/300px-Chinese-grammar-wiki-you-2.jpg" decoding="async" width="300" height="300" srcset="https://resources.allsetlearning.com/gramwiki/images/thumb/2/24/Chinese-grammar-wiki-you-2.jpg/450px-Chinese-grammar-wiki-you-2.jpg 1.5x, https://resources.allsetlearning.com/gramwiki/images/thumb/2/24/Chinese-grammar-wiki-you-2.jpg/600px-Chinese-grammar-wiki-you-2.jpg 2x" /></a></div>
</div> 
<p>When you're getting descriptive, you may find yourself wanting to use multiple <a href="Adjective" title="Adjective">adjectives</a> at a time. The character 又 (yòu) can be used to give two qualities to something. Using the double 又 (yòu) structure is like saying that something is "both… and…" in English. 
</p>
<div id="toc" class="toc"><input type="checkbox" role="button" id="toctogglecheckbox" class="toctogglecheckbox" style="display:none" /><div class="toctitle" lang="en" dir="ltr"><h2>Contents</h2><span class="toctogglespan"><label class="toctogglelabel" for="toctogglecheckbox"></label></span></div>
<ul>
<li class="toclevel-1 tocsection-1"><a href="&quot;Both_A_and_B&quot;_with_&quot;you&quot;#Structure"><span class="tocnumber">1</span> <span class="toctext">Structure</span></a></li>
